      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2013-12-17T20:08:10Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>Railway Inspection and Transparency Act - Directs the Federal Railroad Administration (FRA) to require each railroad carrier to arrange for an independent inspection by a professional engineer of: (1) all railroad bridges at least biennially, and (2) all railroad signals and switches at least semiannually.</p> <p>Requires: (1) each railroad carrier to provide inspection results to the FRA, and (2) the FRA to make those results available to the public.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2013-11-20T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
